Commentary: slog swept in the air, and Hasan makes no mistake at midwicket! Hendricks had looked to sweep Shadab as soon as he came on, but the shot has proved his undoing, the ball taking the top edge and presenting Hasan, at midwicket on the edge of the circle, with a fairly straightforward chance. He holds on, despite a bit of wobble in the breeze as the ball came down, and Pakistan have struck

Commentary: given caught behind but Rassie reviews. Looking to reverse sweep a full ball outside off that's turning away. He was pretty low so I imagine there'll be contact of the bat with the ground. This could be a tricky one...yes there is contact with the ground, but long after the ball has passed the bat. We'll be saved some confusion then. The ball is close to the forearm as it rises into Sarfraz's gloves...and the forerarm is where there is a minute disturbance. Commentary: this one slips out as a full toss, but Shoaib can only manufacture a single to long off

Commentary: pushed down the ground for a regulation single

Commentary: nice and full from Pretorius, Shoaib tapping to cover

Commentary: shorter this time, but it's outside off and Shoaib stands tall to guide the ball to third man for one

Commentary: chance for a run out! This was tapped to cover and the batsmen just set off. Cover swooped, and had he picked it up cleanly there might have been some danger

Commentary: wrong 'un from Tahir, but Hafeez has seen it all before, jumping out like Trumper to meet the ball on the full and hammer it way over wide long on. Rabada was waiting for the catch, instead he watched the ball sail over his head

Commentary: punched through cover

Commentary: there's a cry of 'catch it!' as Shoaib's drive flies in the air but wide of any fielder

Commentary: landing on leg stump and spinning across Hafeez, who taps back down the wicket

Commentary: and he starts with a cutter aimed at middle stump that spits a little off the track, Shoaib copping a blow to the thigh

Commentary: bowled 'im! South Africa needed a wicket, and Phehlukwayo has struck. The delivery was on a length, just outside off, and Shoaib was just trying to guide it down to third man, as has been done umpteen times tonight. But the ball nipped in to him off the surface, cramping him for room, and ultimately sliding off the bat and straight onto the stumps
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Shoaib Malik, OUT

Commentary: Sarfraz is off the mark straight away, playing the shot Shoaib was trying to play, but this time easing it down to third man for one

Commentary: Phehlukwayo loses his line just a little, and Hafeez seizes on the opportunity to glance the ball through midwicket. This fairly pinged off the middle of the bat, didn't over hit it, just timed to the rope

Commentary: full and straight, and Sarfraz pushes it back to the bowler

Commentary: Tahir's off, arms spread in celebration! The ball was pushed through flat and fast, but it gripped in the surface to beat the outside edge and hit Sarfraz on the back thigh. Up goes the finger, but not so fast! Sarfraz reviews it. Where did this pitch? On middle and leg. Where is it headed? For the stumps. Three reds after the review, and Sarfraz has to go. Two quick wickets!
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sarfraz Ahmed lbw b Imran Tahir 1 (4m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

Commentary: Shadab stretches forward to sweep, but the ball bounces off his thigh and towards short third man as they pinch a single

Commentary: bad ball, great shot! Hafeez eases the pressure by walking across to off stump to paddle a full toss outside leg stump down to the fine leg boundary. Olivier must have been aiming for the yorker, but that would have been a big wide had Hafeez not hit it

Commentary: what a shot! This is ice cold from Hafeez. Olivier is trying to do too much, and another attempted yorker slips out as a full toss. Hafeez spots it early and chips the ball over mid off with a checked drive, wonderfully executed

Commentary: nudged into the leg side, and there's room for a single that keeps Hafeez on strike

Commentary: aerial once more off the bat of Hafeez, but this time it's a pull of rather more authority, the ball dropping well in front of the square leg fielder

Commentary: what's happened here? It's another short one from Olivier, and the ball hits Hafeez on the shoulder on its way through to Klaasen. No major drama

Commentary: they're level! Olivier's bouncer terrorized Pakistan through three Tests, but this track doesn't have the same sort of pace and bounce and Hafeez dismisses the short ball from his presence with a crisp pull. Mickey is smiling on the balcony. So is Sarfraz

Commentary: and there it is, Shadab digs a yorker out down the ground and the job is done, Pakistan win by five wickets with five balls to spare
